In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims May 10 through May 16, 2015, as National Women's Health Week. He emphasizes the importance of quality, affordable healthcare as a fundamental right for all individuals, regardless of gender. The Affordable Care Act is highlighted as a means of achieving this right for women across the country, saving money for families and saving lives. The article also mentions the benefits of the law, such as preventing gender-based premium differences and denying coverage based on pre-existing conditions. It emphasizes expanded access to preventive care and the importance of eliminating disparities in health outcomes. The Obama Administration is committed to strengthening the Affordable Care Act and ensuring access to crucial services for all women. The article concludes by encouraging Americans to celebrate the progress made in protecting women's health and promoting awareness, prevention, and educational activities to improve women's health.